R E A L I T Y テレビ.title: 接続中
R E A L I T Y テレビ.artist: R E A L I T Y テレビ
R E A L I T Y テレビ.about:
connect_with_one_another
-------------------------------
接続中, which translates to “connecting”, is exactly what this album is about. Whether it be connecting with old or new friends, connecting with a lover, or just connecting with yourself. This album is about keeping in touch with the people around you and connecting yourself with reality.
“create_new_i-be_profile” was the first song completed for the album. The title pays homage to one of my favourite filmmakers, Ryan Trecartin. ‘I-be Area’ is such a wild and interesting movie that has this proto-vaporwave aesthetic that I think fans of this genre would enjoy. A sample of his work will show up later in the album as well!
Now onto the song itself… I was inspired to create this track after hearing “数学” by Macintosh Plus. The way they incorporate the saxophone sample over a completely different song was so inspiring to me, so I decided to try my own take at that. The main sample used in this song is “I Wanna Make Love To You” by Yours Truly, and the saxophone sample that pops up throughout is “Feels So Good” by Chuck Mangione. The latter is one of my all time favourite jazz songs. So when it came to choosing a saxophone instrumental I knew exactly where to pull from!
“stronger_with_friends” is another unique song on the album. I was inspired to create it because Metric is playing a show here in Calgary later this year and so I decided to dive deeper into their discography. I found the song “Clone” and thought it would be cool to vaporize, so I did! The chaotic sample you hear in the middle is audio from a short film called “junior war, 2013” by, you guessed it, Ryan Trecartin. This is the second time I’ve sampled this film for a song, the first being on the track “my love 2013” from the album “things are quieter now”.
The theme of connection for this album was inspired by the album art itself. After listening through the some of the songs I quickly realized this album is definitely a late night drive type album, or taking a walk under a low hanging sun type album. The cover I had initially made for the album didn’t really match the vibe of the album so I had scrapped it and started over. After scrolling around the net for a few days I found this incredible picture of some sort of y2k era video game that reminded me of an old tony hawk game from my childhood. Hawaii from THUG to be exact. The picture, that you are now familiar with, had digital palm trees backed by a beautiful palette of pink and orange—the perfect aesthetic for the album. It just needed a lil something extra and the cover was done! Because my mind had temporarily stumbled down the tony hawks video game series rabbit hole, I thought of something that might be the perfect thing to accompany the backdrop… The cellphone from THAW! It matched the cover so well and after adding the album title to the phone, the album cover was now complete!
The rest of the album was completed soon after the cover was done. The finishing touch was adding the voicemail sample to the start of the last track “i’m_the_1_4_u”. For the longest time I couldn’t figure out how to close out the album, but adding that little cherry on top was the final piece of the puzzle sliding into place. This album was a blast to make and I hope it’s just as fun of a listen! And thank you :)
Bonus facts:
- The words in the titles are all connected via underscores to further drive home the theme of connection
- the sample used in “telecommunication_system” is from a  hotels.com  ad. It kept popping up when I was looking for samples on YouTube and I got annoyed by it. Buuuut it kinda matched the vibe and because I heard it so damn much it became an ear worm and so I ended up using it!

My previous life seems so egregious now that I am here! Nothing to worry about anymore. Please consider joining me here. We have achieved utopia and I just know you’d love it! I promise everything will be okay.”
- Grace

“Everything is perfect here. Everyone has their place. Everyone is happy and healthy and nobody wants to leave except for a few poisoned apples. We know the truth. The outside world can think what they will but we know what is reality. Jim can see it and he will protect us and guide us on the path to righteousness. Please join us now before it’s too late!”
- Grace
IV. Death
“The world is corrupt and is a blazing inferno surrounding us. We can no longer live in such inhumanity. We have decided that the only path to peace is through the death of our physical being. They can no longer corrupt us on the other side. They can no longer infiltrate our society on the other side. We can all live together in peace and harmony on the other side. It’s not too late to join us but you must take the proper steps if you want to reach eternal peace. Much love and I can’t wait for us to be together again.”
- Grace

R E A L I T Y テレビ.title: Live from the Royal Canadian Legion
R E A L I T Y テレビ.artist: R E A L I T Y テレビ
R E A L I T Y テレビ.about:
Around the start of July 2021 I was listening to some Spyro Gyra on the way to work. Nothing crazy right? Just some groovy Jazz before work. Well, as I was jamming out to the song “Islands in the Sky” I thought to myself how perfect this song would be to make into vaporwave. Although I was relatively new to vaporwave at the time I still understood the basics of classic vaporwave. When I got home that day, I opened up my laptop and started messing around with “Islands in the Sky” in a video editor. A few hours went by and I found myself with my own vaporwave song! I’ve always loved vaporwave since I discovered it but it was at this moment when I realized it was possible to make myself!
Now let’s fast forward 1 whole year… It’s now June 2022 and I’ve been making music almost non-stop since that moment. I was just chillin’ when I received an email from a local arts dude. The email was asking if I could play some of my tunes at an art gallery. And without hesitation, I jumped on the opportunity and agreed! The next month consisted of sifting through my whole discography and picking out the songs for the track list. After a long deliberation, I finally came up with the 40 minute set. After I gathered all the tracks for the show, I came up with a plan to make the setlist into a CD! So I got to work. I made the album cover and burned the songs onto some old discs. After hours of arts and crafts, I was finally met with the final product. A beautiful physical piece of my own music! Almost exactly 1 year after creating my first song, I was making my own merch for my first live show! I never would have expected to be here right now and I definitely wouldn’t be here without all the people who have listened over the past 12 months. Thank You. I can’t express enough what all of this means to me...
… I wrote all that right before the live show back in 2022 and to this day I am still incredibly grateful for all of you that have stuck around! This last year and a half has been an absolute rollercoaster for me and making music is the only thing that has kept me sane. Here’s to you and thanks again. :)
With all that being said, Here is the live set I played on July 2nd 2022 at the STARRY DYNAMO! Enjoy! <3

R E A L I T Y テレビ.artist: R E A L I T Y テレビ
R E A L I T Y テレビ.about:
“imagine u & i @ southcentre. a place 2 hang out with friends. a place 2 shop any online store u desire. a place 2 be anything u want 2 be! choose & customize ur avatar, connect 2 the net, then shop endlessly online with ur friends! join the internet craze now & shop @ southcentre!”
About the album:
If “angel girl”, the album before this one, was my getting dumped album. Then “u & i @ southcentre” is my getting back on track album. I was going through a very turbulent time when those albums were released, hence the plethora of emo song titles.
Most of the song’s compositions were inspired by Chuck Person’s Ecco Jams Vol. 1. That album was on repeat during that time and so my music reflected it! Songs like the opening track, “when u r loved <3”, “ur my everything”, “can we be lovers??”, and “got 2 get someone” are all direct influences from that Ecco Jams style.
The theme for this album is virtual reality. Imagine a mall that you can shop online with your friends all while in the comfort of your own home! I was inspired for this, and many other albums, from the movie WALL-E. The idea that technology has advanced so much that humans have slipped away from reality itself and now live in virtual reality fascinates me to no end. Other albums that have this theme are “仮想ロビーONLINE!”, “CyberMall.com” and “The Digital Dimension”.
Bonus facts:
- the small interludes you hear interspersed throughout are from the famous evergreen collection of Kmart cassette tapes!
- Southcentre is a mall here in Calgary that I have now become super familiar with in the last year and so I used it for the title!
- The picture used for the album cover is from the PC game “Mall Tycoon 2”
